---
import Button from './Button.astro';
import SubscribeButton from './SubscribeButton.astro';
---

<div class="about-me">
  <!-- Contact Section First -->
  <div class="contact-section">
    <h3 class="section-title">CONTACT</h3>
    <p>If you want to talk about any of this, feel free to reach out via <a href="mailto:hello@kttlsaa.com">hello@kttlsaa.com</a></p>
  </div>
  
  <div class="social-section">
    <h3 class="section-title">SOCIAL</h3>
    <ul class="social-list">
      <li><a href="https://twitter.com/kttlsaa">Twitter</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/kttlsaa">GitHub</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://are.na/kttlsaa">are.na</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://scholar.social/@kttlsaa">Mastodon</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  
  <!-- About Me Section -->
  <div class="about-section">
    <h3 class="section-title">MORE ABOUT ME</h3>
    <div class="intro">
      <p>As a designer I make things, and these things are, by definition, artifacts of culture. They use and exist in relation to (sub-)cultural codes, symbols and myths. Because of this, I am interested in cultural studies, sociology, semiotics and aesthetics.</p>
      
      <p class="philosophy-paragraph">I want to create products that are meaningful, personal, generous, considerate, ethical and empowering.</p>
      
      <p class="philosophy-paragraph">As a designer I am naturally interested in how we can understand and react to complexity in situations, systems and problems. In particular, I like thinking (and talking) about the expression and development of thoughts and ideas through prototyping, modeling and notation systems.</p>
      
      <p class="philosophy-paragraph">I want to take part in the discourse of my discipline and try to contribute to a design theory that is rooted in practice.</p>
      
      <p class="philosophy-paragraph">I believe in good minimalism over bad complexity — but also in good complexity over good minimalism.</p>
      
      <p class="philosophy-paragraph">Even though I consider myself a designer, I have found code to be the best medium to express my ideas.</p>
      
      <p>In my day to day work I've been mostly focused on product design and strategy, digital-first branding and the creation and maintenance of design systems. Before coming to Hamburg I studied Interaction Design at <a href="https://www.hfg-gmuend.de/en/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">University of Design Schwäbisch Gmünd</a> in southern Germany.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <!-- Add a larger bottom spacer -->
  <div class="bottom-spacer" aria-hidden="true"></div>
</div>

<style>
  .about-me {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-l);
    max-width: 65ch;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding-bottom: var(--space-4xl);
  }
  
  .intro p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-m);
    line-height: 1.7;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }
  
  .section-title {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-s);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  
  .social-list {
    list-style-type: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-m);
  }
  
  .social-list li {
    margin-right: var(--space-m);
  }
  
  .philosophy-paragraph {
    font-weight: 500;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
  
  .bottom-spacer {
    height: var(--space-xl);
  }
  
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about-me {
      gap: var(--space-m);
      padding-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
    }
    
    .intro p {
      font-size: 1rem;
      margin-bottom: var(--space-s);
    }
    
    .section-title {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }
    
    .social-list {
      gap: var(--space-s);
    }
    
    .social-list li {
      margin-right: var(--space-s);
    }
  }
  
  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .about-me {
      gap: var(--space-s);
    }
    
    .intro p {
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }
    
    .section-title {
      font-size: 0.9rem;
    }
    
    .social-list {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: var(--space-xs);
    }
    
    .social-list li {
      margin-right: 0;
    }
  }
</style>
